to me, the `RegEx` approach seems the best approach.

Assuming that you do not know exactly how many digits your IDs have (quote: _followed by a few digits_), you could through the whole string and catch what&#39;s inside parenthesis:

    s = &quot;Bob Rob Smith (L1234567), John Doe (k12345678)&quot;

    res = []
    word = &#39;&#39;
    open = False
    for x in s:
        if x == &#39;(&#39;:
            open = True
            continue
        if x == &#39;)&#39;:
            open = False
            res.append(word)
            word = &#39;&#39;
        if open:
            word += x
    
    print(res)

